A mantâ€™s homage.

The following memorandum is written in a hand ol the 3 fifteenth century on a blank space of sol. 163 b:

Whan a tenant shal do his homage he shal holde his handys togidir, and put them in his lordys handyS, And shal sey in this forme that lolwith: 1 becom your man sro this day forward lor tho londes that l hold os you, And trew leyth shal bere to you ageyns al personoe that may leve, by knythis scenice, savyng the seyth that I ovh (owe) to the kyng and odyr that I have don homage to.
